HARDWARE LICENSE - CERN-OHL-S-2.0
==================================

The following files and designs are licensed under CERN-OHL-S-2.0:

- All KiCad project files (*.kicad_pro, *.kicad_sch, *.kicad_pcb)
- Schematic designs and circuit diagrams
- PCB layouts and manufacturing files (Gerbers, drill files)
- Bill of Materials (BOM)
- Component footprints and symbols
- Hardware design documentation in Hardware.md and Requirements.md

Full license text: https://ohwr.org/cern_ohl_s_v2.txt

CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal (CERN-OHL-S-2.0)

This license is designed to provide freedom to use, study, modify, and share
hardware designs. Any derivative works must be shared under the same license
terms (strongly reciprocal/copyleft).

Key permissions:
- Use the design commercially or non-commercially
- Study and analyze the design
- Modify the design and create derivative works
- Distribute the design and derivative works

Key requirements:
- Make design files available when distributing hardware
- Share modifications under CERN-OHL-S-2.0
- Preserve copyright and license notices
- Document changes made to the design

For the complete license terms, see:
https://ohwr.org/cern_ohl_s_v2.txt

